1�How do you respond?We've got to go in.It's best to wait for them.
1�To think, our foe lies beyond this door...
1�But Morimar and Darrcuiln aren't here yet.
1� , remember how I made you promise not to go on without me? What would it say about me if we went behind his back and did the same thing?
1�  and Arciela. How many moons has it been?
1�I see that one of your ragtag entourage is conspicuously absent.
1�Men are born into this world whole, but their spirits live on even as their bodies crumble into dust.
1�They float through time and space--some days, some weeks, some centuries--until they are eventually given life again.
1�Spirits never know release from their torment, all owing to the gloom that resides within each of us.
1�And what do they carry with them as they revive anew?Nothing. They are ethereal strings, stretching from existence to pointless existence.
1�Yet if we try to tie the ends together, to close the circle, we discover only that they extend farther than our hands can reach.
1�I pity those lost souls who will never attain true awareness, and thus I have no choice but to snuff each lone candle out.
1�And once that task is done, I will rebuild a new, more natural order.
1�How is that evil? By bringing death, I create new life.
1�And the only way to save a spirit is to annihilate it.
1�Despite your endless meandering, you occasionally give life to exceptional individuals. An ??awakening.??
1�Maybe you are a sign, sent to guide me on the right path. There are things that even someone with endless hosts like myself does not know.
1�Will you be the ones to open the gates to paradise?
1�You have come to stop me, have you not?
1�Do the lot of you not realize how absurd this is? Surely you cannot mean to succeed.
h!�It would serve you better to put more weight into your blade than your war cries.
1�Did someone show you how to resist me for so long? Tell me, Morimar--what have you learned?
1�What unworldly forces has the betrayer given you?Hahaha, survive you might, but your soul will never again know solace!
1�After all, you stand in my domain now.
1�Congratulations on breaking the blood sigils. It's more than I'd expected.
1�I'm eminently aware that the betrayer had a hand in this.
1�A toast, then! To the success of our heroes!
1�Ha! What do you think your little playtime bought you?
1�A chance to stand on equal footing? Is that it?
1�Perhaps I should pat you on the head like the simpletons you are.
1�But it's pointless knowing that now, because in precious moments I'll be making trinkets out of your bones.
1�For a man with an eternity to spend, I've very little patience.
1�What've I done? Oh, your mewling amuses me so.
1�You want him back, don't you? Yet you can't say those four little words.
1�Hahaha! I've treated you a bit more beastly than you truly are. My apologies.
1�What a faithful little pet, cowering about wanting his master's body returned.
1�And what would you do with it? Climb a grassy knoll and bury it overlooking the ocean?
1�Or would you leave the corpse in a dirty field for the vultures to gnaw at his flesh?
1�Too bad for you, then, that neither will happen.
1�You pitiful fools are dumb enough to believe that I'd leave so much as a shred of him left?
1�I had expected even your pea-sized brains to know that much.
1�Let's postulate for one minute. Even if I did let him leave with his life, what would he have done?
1�Go scurrying back to his oh-so-faithful companions, weaving a grand tale of his daring escape.
1�But that faint glimmer of hope you held out should have turned into despair.
1�Because your master didn't come back, did he?
1�Oho, I should've given you more credit. It's exactly as you think.
1�His death throes were silenced by these two hands.
1�He spewed to the last that he did it to save his friends and drew his last breath, alone, in a struggle that was anything but valiant.
1�Do you know how hordes of rats spill out of the walls when a sturdy vessel careens over?
1� This one got a bit stuck along the way. Where his friends found higher ground, he found only watery asphyxiation.
1�Could you picture a more comical end?
1�To have lived years--centuries!--only to die in ignominy.
1�And what does he have to show for it?
1�A man with no value in life finding no value in death.
h!�Oh, now that's a sight I haven't seen in ages.
1�That shine...using your soul to fuel your rage!
r>�I was right the first time. Your mind speaks the tongue of man, but your vocalizations are those of a mere monstrosity.
1�It's high time you, too, fell into the abyss.
1�And I have come to release all souls from wandering aimlessly in the dark!
1�Is by ridding myself of all vestiges of humanity!
1�I must shed this skin and abandon the frailty of mankind!
1�( , you heard him! We have to escape before it is too late!)
1�(Princess, you heard him...if we do not leave now, then we all die!)
1�Stop spittin' out filth and fight like a man!
1�Maybe I'm not half the man I once was, but I've got wisdom now I didn't then!
1�Don't pretend ta be all high and mighty with--
1�Darrcuiln, ya gonna stand there agape, or get yer hide outta here like I asked!?
1�Go! I can only protect ya for so long!
1�And you two--I need ya to trust me on this one! Throwin' a bunch of words at ya as explanation isn't gonna help!
1�Flee while you can! I've got a little someone taking care of things fer me!
d.�And where's all yer trust in m
1�I'd not have it any other way!
1�Cling to my wings, seekers of Adoulin.
1�Stand, Princess. Now is not the time to falter.
1�The gate connecting these two worlds is unstable. Tartarus threatens to consume this entire place.
..�...And no matter how much I loathe him, and shall continue to despise him for all time...
1�...I cannot allow you to extinguish the small fire he awakened in my heart when first we met.
1�<The World Tree oooversees all life. Let me lend them but a fraction of her vitality.>
1�<Motheeer, grant them your bounty, that they may find the strength to overcome.>
1�And you, young cub, are the very image of your honored father.
1�People do not swear fealty to a king. A king swears fealty to his people.
1�But your deep-green eyes and hair of purest silver... Our daughter looked much the same.
1�It was with heavy heart I witnessed the years of trials faced by our nation. Yet seeing you this day has eased my burden.
1�You have an older brother--Ygnas, was it not? The man's stubbornness rivals my own.
1�And lest you ask--yes, that was my doing.
1�He is a scrappy one.And the curse that bound him is no more.
1�His path is now his own to walk.
1�My knight most true, Ulbuka continues to need your service.
1�Enough with royal fiats. Sajj'aka, your time is now.
1�We shall not meet again in this time. Watch over my people, always.
1�You have protected my descendants--nay, the entirety of my nation--and followed our call to this very spot.
1�You leave miracles in your wake. Yggdrasil is reborn, Sajj'aka is whole, and by the grace of Altana you stand before us today.
1�All those many years ago, we pledged that our deaths would serve a greater purpose. That oath takes form at last.
1�Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya?You got nothin' on me, ?[man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
1�Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky!Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
1�Do you want to hear a story?No, thank you.Let's hear one.
1�What story would you like to be told?On second thought, maybe later.The Key to the Turris.Reckoning.Abomination(pt.1).Abomination(pt.2).
1�Oh...Well, if that's the case, I'm outta here.
